curl - HTTP client
Executable: /bin/curl.sh
Alias: curl

DESCRIPTION
  Performs an HTTP request via
  the CC: Tweaked http API.
  Prints the response body to
  stdout or to a file.

USAGE
  curl <url>
  curl -X POST -d body url
  curl -H 'Accept: text/plain' url
  curl -o out.txt url

OPTIONS
  -X method
    HTTP method
    (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE,
    PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS,
    TRACE).
  -H 'Name: Value'
    Add a request header.
    May be repeated.
  -d body
    Send a request body. The
    method becomes POST when
    not set explicitly.
  -o file
    Write the response body
    to the given file instead
    of stdout.
  -i
    Print the HTTP status
    code and response headers
    before the body.
  -s
    Silent mode. Suppresses
    summary output when
    saving to a file.
  --timeout seconds
    Request timeout passed to
    http.get when running on
    CC: Tweaked 1.105 or
    newer.

NOTES
  The HTTP API must be
  enabled in the CC: Tweaked
  server config. curl checks
  via minux.hasHttpSupport()
  and exits with an error if
  HTTP is disabled.

SEE ALSO
  apt
  ping
